      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PAW OLYMPUS (4) goes very well this trip starting 10 times for four wins and two minors. Recorded a neck win (22.26) in a Grade 5 last time at Warrnambool. Looks suited and should go close. NOT SORRY (2) finished in the minors last start over the 425m at Bendigo but ran a solid 24.02 last start. This tougher but looks a leading chance again. SUPER SYMON (7) was out of the placings last time when fifth at this track (23.74) but did record best time of the card when winning four back. Form here at the trip sound including two wins. The form from his last run stacks up well. A forward showing wouldn't surprise. THERMAL HEAT (1) will be hard to beat despite making her debut at this circuit.",
